added.title: The Cast
added.description: After breaking his leg, Robin is confined to his room and spies through a telescope.

added.title: Superhero Feud
added.description: Control Freak pits the Titans against the DC Superhero Girls to determine who is the best team in the universe.

added.title: I Am Chair
added.description: During a stressful trip to the mall, Robin finds peace in a massage chair.

added.title: The Cycle
added.description: Gumball, Darwin and Anais discover that Mr Wilson has been picking on their Dad for most of his life; ever since he humiliated Richard with a high school prank. The kids try to work Dad through it but when their efforts fail, they realize that getting back at Mr Wilson is the only way to break the cycle.

added.title: The Stars
added.description: When Dad gives Larry's hairdresser a bad review for saying he's bald, he gets offered a free haircut. This inspires Gumball and Darwin to go on a reviewing spree across town, forcing Larry to give them stuff with the threat of a bad review. Just because the customer is always right doesn't mean that what they're doing isn't wrong.

added.title: The Grades
added.description: Miss Simian discovers a failed test from Gumball's past that brings down his grade point average. This means he has to retake kindergarten all over again, much to her delight. But by demoting him Miss Simian has inadvertently brought herself down, and they're left with no choice but to team up if they want things back to normal.

added.title: The Diet
added.description: Gumball and Darwin discover the reason Dad's diet wasn't working was that he was actually on ten diets and eating a meal for each of them. They eventually manage to help him lose weight, but Richard's newfound buffness also brings out his more obnoxious side.

added.title: The Ex
added.description: Gumball discovers that Rob, his old nemesis, is "neme-seeing" someone else now. Devastated that Rob has fallen out of hate with him, Gumball refuses to accept that his ex-nemesis has moved on and does his best to sabotage Rob's blossoming relationship with his new foe, Banana Joe.

added.title: Ace of Squares
added.description: Craig vows to make the game of Four Square fun again by challenging its most dominant player!

added.title: Doorway to Helen
added.description: Craig makes a long distance connection with a kid that loves the creek as much as he does.

added.title: The Last Kid in the Creek
added.description: A terrible curse leaves Craig as the only kid in the creek.

added.title: The Climb
added.description: Craig's phone gets stuck in Mt. Sycamore, the tallest tree in the creek!

added.title: High Baby Fashion
added.description: The Bears enter Panda into a fashion contest, but he's got some fierce competition when Madam Malin and Madeline show up!

added.title: Teddi Bear
added.description: In an endless junkyard the Bears meet Teddi, a sentient teddy bear.

added.title: A Gross Worm
added.description: The Bears help Unica return an endangered alien worm to its home.

added.title: A Real Crayon
added.description: The Bears find a mysterious crayon that has the power to make anything they draw become REAL.

added.title: Witches
added.description: The Bears accidentally summon three mysterious witches and have to figure out how to get them back home.

added.title: Bananas & Cheese
added.description: Duncan is determined to stop the musical duo Bananas & Cheese from coming to the daycare.

added.title: Inglorious Toddlers
added.description: Owen fears he's about to lose his BFF Noah to a gifted military school.

added.title: Not Without My Fudgy Lumps
added.description: Noah tries to rescue the chocolates Owen forgot outside.

added.title: Paint That a Shame
added.description: Leshawna creates a paint balloon fight to decide who gets to come with her to an amusement park.

added.title: Snots Landing
added.description: Beth gets Courtney's diorama furniture stuck up her nose and Courtney needs it back before the diorama contest judge arrives.

added.title: Lowlifes
added.description: Apple & Onion cannot allow themselves to be viewed by society- and more importantly by smug old Chicken Nugget-as lowlifes.

added.title: Falafel's Car Keys
added.description: Apple & Onion are deemed responsible enough to borrow Falafel's car for their first road trip together. Nothing will go wrong, and they're going to make sure of that… by getting some practice in.

added.title: Sneakerheads
added.description: Apple & Onion need a Last Will and Testament if they are to protect their belongings from the state.

added.title: Filthy Rich
added.description: What does it take to be truly content? Whatever it takes, Apple and Onion are going to achieve it.

added.title: Truffle Season
added.description: It's Truffle Season, Apple and Onion are Truffle Hunters and they will stop at nothing to taste a truffle.

added.title: Moor Fogg
added.description: Team Tennyson goes international in the Omni-Copter and the first stop is for a hike in the Scottish Highlands, but the weather isn't just bad, it's foggy, and that means one thing and one thing only: the return of The Fogg!

added.title: King of the Castle
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max next travel to Castle Bishopbrook to visit a distant relative who's royalty, but when Ben encounters a "ghost" at the haunted home, it turns out to actually be his new rival, Kevin 11, throwing even more twisted aliens his way: Thornblade, Undertow, and Dark Matter!

added.title: Speechless on the Seine
added.description: While in Paris, France, Ben catches Zombozo robbing the Louvre, but when Zombozo hypnotizes Ben to remain speechless, Ben must navigate a foreign land like a mime in order to stop the criminal clown and his travelling circus.

added.title: Don't Touch
added.description: Team Tennyson checks out a Samurai Museum in Tokyo, where Ben is too impatient to wait out the Calligraphy experience for the more exciting sounding Samurai one. But when a dangerous Samurai sword is stolen from the exhibit, Ben must take on its thief, the new Big Bad in town, the Forever Knight.

added.title: Big in Japan
added.description: During a tour of the Japanese Robotics Museum, Ben finds hero-gone-wrong Tim Buktu "trying to save" Tokyo from a Dragon. Has Tim finally turned over a new leaf, or is this just another one of his half-baked plans to play the part of hero?

added.title: And Then There Were None
added.description: Vilgax and Eon team up to wipe out every Ben in every dimension!

added.title: And Then There Was Ben
added.description: Professor Paradox unites the good Bens from across all dimensions to take on Vilgax, Eon, and the evil Bens in the ultimate showdown!

added.title: The Vengers
added.description: Billy Billions, Kangaroo Kommando, and Captain Nemesis team up to take down Ben, and claim his place as protector of Bellwood?!?

added.title: Cough It Up
added.description: Psyphon and a gang of bounty hunters are after Argit, who is in possession of a dangerous weapon!

added.title: The Rooters of All Evil
added.description: Meet the Rooters, the Black Ops wing of the Plumbers from the Null Void. They've come looking for someone close to Ben, and they mean business!

added.title: Blukic and Driba Go to Area 51
added.description: A mysterious Galvan arrives and demands Blukic and Driba to give back a super powerful weapon needed to stop a threat to Earth.

added.title: No Honor Among Bros
added.description: Rook is under the influence of Fistrick's "bro" essence, and starts to act like a bro. Can he and Ben infiltrate an alien fight club to claim the Golden Fist? (Introducing Slix Vigma, alien promoter.)

added.title: Universe vs. Tennyson
added.description: Ben gets dragged into intergalactic court by the other Celestialsapiens (Alien Xs) for recreating the universe (back in "So Long and Thanks for All the Smoothies").

added.title: Weapon XI Part 1
added.description: Kevin and Argit attempt to warn the amalgam kids about the Rooters intentions meanwhile Ben, Rook, and Gwen set off to find Kevin and land themselves in the Null Void!

added.title: Weapon XI Part 2
added.description: The Rooters have seemingly turned Kevin and the Amalgam kids against Ben. Can Rook and Gwen help him overcome the opposition and escape the Null Void?

added.title: Joking Victim
added.description: When Lars pawns off all his work on Sadie, Steven helps out by working a shift at the Big Donut.

added.title: Steven and the Stevens
added.description: Steven needs a musical partner for an upcoming show, and uses a time travel device to recruit the perfect bandmate, HIMSELF!

added.title: Monster Buddies
added.description: Steven accidentally releases a monster from a gem bubble and attempts to tame its wild, violent instincts.

added.title: An Indirect Kiss
added.description: When Amethyst cracks her gemstone, Steven and the Crystal Gems go on a mission to heal her.

added.title: Mirror Gem
added.description: Steven befriends a magical mirror that can mysteriously communicate with him.

added.title: Five More Short Graybles
added.description: Finn and Jake stick their thumbs in everything. Marceline tries to find her way to Wizard Bill's Music Shop. Ice King gets a new bride.

added.title: All the Little People
added.description: Magic Man secretly slips Finn a bag filled with miniature versions of Finn and all his friends.

added.title: Jake the Dad
added.description: Jake's a daddy, but being a father and keeping his rainicorn pups from killing themselves or each other is a lot harder than he imagined.

added.title: Bad Little Boy
added.description: The princesses are sick and tired of Ice King's crazy Fionna & Cake stories, so Marceline stops by the Ice Kingdom to show him how it's done.

added.title: Expert or Liar
added.description: Rigby wants to redeem himself by winning on "Expert or Liar."

added.title: Catching the Wave
added.description: Pops wants to catch a wave.

added.title: Gold Watch
added.description: Benson has to get to work on time so he can win a gold watch.

added.title: Paint Job
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to paint a house.

added.title: Take the Cake
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to deliver a cake to Maellard's birthday party.

added.title: Safety First
added.description: Concerned about Puppycorn's propensity to hurt himself constantly, the gang places him into Richard's old Safety Suit. The suit does indeed keep him safe, but when Puppycorn purposefully puts himself in danger the suit goes into lock down, and won't allow him to move. Now the gang must figure out a way to get him out of the Safety Suit.

added.title: Volcano
added.description: A super-grumpy volcano appears in the kingdom, so Unikitty takes the gang on an epic quest to cheer it up with one of FeeBee's flowers before it erupts and destroys the kingdom.

added.title: First Flight
added.description: The gang is taking an airplane trip together, and Hawk is at the helm since today he's taking his captain's license test. However Richard is terrified of flying, so Unikitty & Puppycorn spend the chaotic flight trying to help Rick conquer his fear of flying while Dr Fox joins Hawk in the cockpit to help him pass his test. After a destructive and dangerous flight, Rick makes it safetly back on the ground (after surviving the plane crashing). Hawk fails his test but gets to take it again next week, so the gang is excited for another free flight.

added.title: Cheerleading
added.description: Brock drags Master Frown along to join him in following his dream, to become the Flyer on a cheerleading team. They team up with Unikitty & the gang and go head to head against Really Old Edith and her rival cheer team of meanies. But when the gang finds Brock is too heavy to be the Flyer they're forced to try a bunch of ridiculous ways to get him off the ground.

added.title: Ragtag
added.description: When the kingdom runs out of inspiration, Unikitty takes it on herself to re-inspire the citizens with a riveting game of kickball where she and the gang form a ragtag team of underdogs, who are supposed to win a miraculous unexpected victory against Master Frown, Brock & The Doom Lords. But when the Doom Lords end up stinking at kickball, and the people are uninspired by the good guys' easy victory, Unikitty switches things up and joins the real ragtag team, The Doom Lords, to help lead them to a victory that finally inspires the kingdom.

added.title: The Powerpuff Girls Best Rainy Day Adventure Ever/Just Desserts
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls Best Rainy Day Adventure Ever: It's raining in Townsville and there is no crime or villainy afoot. So the girls must stay inside and come up with their very own Powerpuff adventure./Just Desserts: The Smith Family is back and they want revenge. Harold, Maryanne and the kids become a super villain team and make it their goal to destroy the perfect Powerpuff family.

added.title: Speed Demon/Mojo Jonesin'
added.description: Mojo Jonesin':  When the children of Pokey Oaks become envious of the girls' superpowers, a mysterious figure offers them Chemical X. Now, the girls must fight their own classmates who have powers equal to their own./Speed Demon: The girls accidentally fly at the speed of light and when they arrive home, everything has changed. Fifty years have passed and the world has been taken over by Him.

added.title: Imaginary Fiend/Cootie Gras
added.description: Imaginary Fiend: The new boy in school has a special friend nobody else can see. When this imaginary friend begins destroying the class, the girls must imagine how to stop him./Cootie Gras: Mojo observes that everyone is staying away from little Harry Pitt because he has cooties. So Mojo concocts a plan to keep the girls away by using this cootie-covered boy as bait.

added.title: Mo Job/Pet Feud
added.description: Mo Job: Princess hires Mojo to devise the perfect plan to destroy the girls, who are quite shocked when they find Princess has powers equal to their own./Pet Feud: The Professor creates the perfect little pet. But there's only one catch: he can only be fed once a day. When the girls each feed him, they find that their sweet little friend has become a wild beast!

added.title: Twisted Sister/Cover Up
added.description: Twisted Sister: The girls decide they need some help fighting crime so they create another Powerpuff Girl. But they don't get the combination of sugar, spice and everything nice quite right./Cover Up: Blossom and Bubbles learn that Buttercup has secretly been rubbing a security blanket before every battle to make herself a super fighter. Can the girls convince Buttercup that her strength is within?

added.title: Sister Sitter
added.description: When Blossom and Bubbles get sick, Buttercup volunteers to take care of them for the day.

added.title: Odd Bubbles Out
added.description: When Donny the Unicorn visits, Bubbles becomes jealous of his new friend.

added.title: Presidential Punchout
added.description: When Morbucks enters the Student Body President race, Blossom sinks to her level to secure the win.

added.title: Cheep Thrills
added.description: After finding a baby monster in the park, Bubbles insists on adopting it without considering the consequences!

added.title: Fashion Forward
added.description: When the Fashionistas launch a new line of brainwashing clothing, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop the fashion trend before it's too late.

added.title: Crowbar Jones
added.description: Grizz screens an epic amateur movie he just made for a focus group. But when he notices people are leaving he must figure out ways to keep the audience engaged.

added.title: Kyle
added.description: Nom Nom is reunited with his long lost brother, Kyle.

added.title: Citizen Tabes
added.description: After accidentally wounding an animal, Ranger Tabes quits her job. The Bears do what they can to coax her out of retirement.

added.title: Dance Lessons
added.description: Panda volunteers to be Lucy's partner for a dance contest. But Panda doesn't have the heart to tell Lucy that she's a terrible dancer.

added.title: Icy Nights II
added.description: Ice Bear goes on a late-night adventure to rescue his friend, Yana, from some familiar foes.

added.title: Neighborhood Grill
added.description: Clarence is so troubled by the sight of his teacher in a social setting outside of school, he can't stop himself from intruding on her doomed blind date.

added.title: Belson's Sleepover
added.description: Belson invites Clarence and friends to a sleepover party, with a catch: whoever can survive the night's pranks and scares will win Belson's old Acedia game system!

added.title: Too Gross for Comfort
added.description: Clarence's innocent attempt to ingratiate Chelsea, a girl, into a boys only tree fort puts Sumo in charge of an effort to gross Chelsea out and preserve the status quo.

added.title: Pilot Expansion
added.description: Clarence, Sumo, and Jeff reminisce about the day they first met - although a few of the details are foggy.

added.title: Patients
added.description: Clarence must somehow navigate the mind-numbing boredom of a doctor's office waiting room to earn the ultimate prize - candy from the reception desk candy jar.

added.title: Pizza Steve's Past
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang learn of Pizza Steve's past stint in the food service industry. Pizza Steve wasn't always the Pizza Steve they know and love.

added.title: Broken Boogie
added.description: When the Boogie Man loses his mojo, Uncle Grandpa steps in to help.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa's Uncle Grandpa
added.description: Uncle Grandpa is in trouble! If only he could call an Uncle Grandpa for help.

added.title: Anger Management
added.description: Aunt Grandma's back is causing more trouble for Uncle Grandpa.

added.title: Diggin' A Hole
added.description: Uncle Grandpa digs a hole.

added.title: Racer Seven
added.description: As the ninja prepare for the brutal Speedway Five-Billion race, Lloyd meets a race driver named Seven, who is programmed to lose, but who may hold the key to victory.

added.title: The Speedway Five-Billion
added.description: Unagami's soldiers, the Red Visors, finally discover the secret location of Scott's garage and attack the ninja, who manage to escape with the help of Racer Seven, and enter the spectacular Speedway Five Billion.

added.title: Stop, Drop and Side Scroll
added.description: Our ninja barely have time to mourn the loss of their fallen ninja friends before being thrust into the madness of Terra Domina where Lloyd will have to face an old adversary from his past.

added.title: Ninjago Confidential
added.description: Back in Ninjago City, Zane and Pixal hit the mean streets to track down Milton Dyer, only to discover that things are not what they seem.

added.title: The Prodigal Father
added.description: Zane, kidnapped by the Mechanic, faces Unagami. Master Wu fights to free Zane, while Pixal questions Milton Dyer for information on how to shut down Prime Empire.

added.title: Shun and Lightning/Premonition of a Storm
added.description: Shun and Lightning: Shun and Lightning are on the hunt for a rare Tumpee, when they run into McQ! With all the devices related crimes happening in Los Volmos, Shun decides to investigate to try to get to the bottom of McQ's nefarious dealings./Premonition of a Storm: After a run in with McQ, Shun and Lightning find themselves in a little bit trouble. They're trapped!  Tied up with no Bakugan to help them escape, and no one knows their whereabouts. It will take some big help to help them get out of this mess.

added.title: Superstar Dan/Awesome Brawlers on Vacation
added.description: Superstar Dan: The Awesome Brawler's head to Tokyo for the Bakugan Battle League - Tokyo Edition. While Wynton, Shun, Lia and Lightning see the sites, and enjoy the tastes of Japan, Dan, as the Los Volmos Champion, has official Bakugan Battle League duties and obligations that keep him busy./Awesome Brawlers on Vacation: Lia, Lightning, Shun and Wynton explore the sights of Toyko when a rogue Bakugan shows up and rampages. The Awesome Brawlers have to spring into action, rolling out their Bakugan to stop the rogue enemy before any real damage can be done.

added.title: Bakugan Battle League, Tokyo Edition/Battle Royal
added.description: Bakugan Battle League, Tokyo Edition: It's the start of the Bakugan Battle League - Toyko edition! The first round will be a Battle Royale style competition, where only half the competitors will make it through to the next round. Along with the Awesome brawlers the field of competitors is filled with familiar friends and foes./Battle Royal: The first round of the Bakugan Battle League - Tokyo edition continues. The Awesome Brawler's and their Bakugan battle their way through the challenge and face off against tough competitors.

added.title: The Second Stage Begins/Mechanoids Attack!
added.description: The Second Stage Begins: With half of the brawlers eliminated, the second stage of the Bakugan Battle league begins. This round will be a timed race to the finish, with all kinds of tricks and traps that will slow down even the best brawlers./Mechanoids Attack!: Mechanoids have crashed the second stage of the Bakugan Battle League, causing all kinds of havoc. The Awesome Brawlers will now have to race against the clock, battling competitors and mechanoids if they want to make it through this round.

added.title: The Other Fight
added.description: Eliminated from the Bakugan Battle League, Ajit is airlifted by drone to a massive cargo ship in the middle of Tokyo Bay. Now that he's on board the cargo ship, he must rescue Dan and Drago, and stop whoever is sabotaging the Battle League. Dan and Ajit investigate the mysterious cargo ship that the eliminated brawlers and Bakugan are being held on. Dan races to track down Drago, but along the way runs into a familiar face.

added.title: Crowbar Jones
added.description: Pardo proyecta una película amateur épica que acaba de rodar para un grupo focal. Pero cuando se da cuenta de que la gente se marcha, debe descubrir formas de mantener interesada a la audiencia.

added.title: Kyle
added.description: Nom Nom se reúne con Kyle, su hermano del que estaba distanciado.

added.title: La ciudadana Tabes
added.description: Luego de lastimar por accidente a un animal, la guardabosques Tabes renuncia a su trabajo. Los Osos hacen todo lo posible para persuadirla de jubilarse.

added.title: Lecciones de Baile
added.description: Panda se ofrece como voluntario para ser el compañero de Lucy en un concurso de baile. Pero no se atreve a decirle a Lucy que es una pésima bailarina.

added.title: Noches heladas dos
added.description: Polar sale a una aventura nocturna para rescatar a Yana, su amiga, de unos enemigos familiares.

added.title: Piloto Siete
added.description: Mientras los Ninjas se preparan para la carrera Cinco Billones por Hora, Lloyd conoce a la Piloto Siete quien puede tener la clave de la victoria.

added.title: Carrera Cinco Billones por Hora
added.description: Los soldados de Unagami, los Visores Rojos, finalmente descubren la ubicación secreta del garaje de Scott y atacan a los Ninjas.

added.title: Detenerse, Caer y Girar
added.description: Los Ninjas no han ni llorado la pérdida de sus amigos  caídos cuando ya deben entrar a la locura de Tierra Domina.

added.title: Ninjago Confidencial
added.description: De vuelta en la ciudad de Ninjago, Zane y Pixal salen a las calles para encontrar a Milton Dyer, y descubren que las cosas no son lo que parecen…

added.title: El Padre Prodigo
added.description: Zane, secuestrado por el Mecánico mientras Pixal interroga a Milton Dyer para obtener información sobre cómo cerrar el Primer Imperio.

added.title: La seguridad es primero
added.description: Preocupados por la propensión de Perricornio a lastimarse constantemente, la banda le coloca el viejo traje de seguridad de Richard. El traje lo mantiene a salvo, pero cuando Perricornio se pone en peligro a propósito, el traje se bloquea y le impide moverse. Ahora la banda debe encontrar la manera de sacarlo del traje de seguridad.

added.title: Volcan
added.description: Un volcán súper gruñón aparece en el reino. Por eso, Unikitty lleva a la banda a una misión épica para alegrarlo con una de las flores de FeeBee antes de que entre en erupción y destruya el reino. Pero FeeBee no tiene ganas de compartir sus queridas flores, y trata de sabotear la misión. ¿Será capaz Unikitty de convencerla de los beneficios de compartir para salvar el reino de la destrucción?

added.title: Primer Vuelo
added.description: Cuando la banda hace un viaje en avión, Halcondrilo está al mando ya que hoy da el examen para obtener su licencia de capitán. Como a Richard le da terror volar, Unikitty y Perricornio pasan el caótico vuelo tratando de ayudarlo a vencer su miedo, mientras la Dra. Fox acompaña a Halcondrilo en la cabina para ayudarlo a aprobar su examen.

added.title: Los Porristas
added.description: Brock convence a Master Frown de acompañarlo para hacer realidad su sueño de convertirse en el volador de un equipo de animadoras. Se asocian con Unikitty y la banda y se enfrentan cara a cara con Edith y el equipo de porristas malvados que tienen como rivales. Pero cuando la banda descubre que Brock es demasiado pesado para ser el volador, se ven obligados a intentar un montón de formas ridículas de levantarlo del suelo.

added.title: Campeones por accidente
added.description: Cuando el reino se queda sin inspiración, Unikitty se encarga de volver a inspirar a los ciudadanos con un fascinante juego de kickball en el que ella y la banda forman un equipo de débiles, que se supone que obtendrán una victoria milagrosa e inesperada contra Master Frown, Brock y los Señores de la Muerte. Pero cuando los Señores de la Muerte pierden el partido de kickball, y la gente no se siente inspirada por la victoria fácil de los chicos buenos, Unikitty cambia las cosas y se une al desamparado equipo enemigo para ayudarlos a conseguir una victoria que finalmente inspire al reino.

added.title: Bananas y Queso
added.description: Duncan está decidido a evitar que el dúo Banana y Queso se presente en la guardería.

added.title: Ninos vergonzosos
added.description: Owen teme perder a su mejor amigo Noah que se va a una escuela militar.

added.title: No sin mis choco-lletas
added.description: Noah intenta rescatar los chocolates que Owen olvidó afuera.

added.title: Campeon del Cuadro
added.description: iCraig promete hacer que el juego de Cuatro Cuadros vuelva a ser divertido cuando desafía a su jugador más experto!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Pintura dolorosa
added.description: Leshawna inventa una pelea con globos llenos de pintura para ver quién va al parque de diversiones con ella.

added.title: Portal hacia Helen
added.description: Craig hace una conexión a larga distancia con un niño que ama el Arroyo tanto como él.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Aterrizaje mocoso
added.description: A Beth se le atascan los muebles del diorama de Courtney en la nariz y Courtney tiene que recuperarlos antes de que llegue el juez del concurso de dioramas.

added.title: A escalar
added.description: iEl teléfono de Craig se atasca en el Monte Sicomoro, el árbol más alto del Arroyo!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Don Pellizco
added.description: JP lleva a sus amigos de viaje para encontrar el cangrejo de río más grande del Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Up a Tree
added.description: Finn and Jake are playing catch when Finn accidentally tosses their throwing disc into a gigantic tree.

added.title: Bam's Upgrade
added.description: Feeling neglected after being passed over on missions, Bam asks MOE to install experimental upgrades to curry Batman's favor. But, when Bam's new powers are stronger than he can control, Batman - and the mission - are suddenly in danger!

added.title: Redbird's Bogus Beach Day
added.description: Redbird gets excited when he learns that Batman and Robin are taking him and Bam for a drive up the coast! But when the Joker and his van Prank show up unexpectedly and ruin Redbird's beach day plans, Bam helps him realize that even though things didn't go exactly as planned, they still had a great day!

added.title: Smash House
added.description: The Looney Builders learn that Taz accidentally destroyed his house, so they set out to build him a new one that's smash-proof.

added.title: Play Day
added.description: When the Looney Builders build themselves a playground, Daffy gets so excited about his section that he takes all the supplies for himself.

added.title: Yip Yip, Book Book!/Stick to It!
added.description: It's the Pretty Big All City Read and Izzy and Barb are ready, that is, until all the books go missing!/Pretty Big City finds itself in a sticky situation when the factory starts spewing super sticky slime everywhere!

added.title: The Treasure of Treetop Woods/Zee Makes an Amazing Maze!
added.description: Ranger Nat's hike turns to adventure when he finds a treasure map. The only problem is that he can't read it./Zee and MacBarm are setting up their corn maze with the help of Zee's Zee Mobile… that is, until it breaks down inside the maze.

added.title: Bring it On Beresford
added.description: On Plant-A-Tree Day on Sodor, Thomas and Diesel both want to deliver the most impressive pine for the holiday, but they'll have to compete by delivering all the other trees first. When Thomas wins the race and the pine is loaded onto his flatcar, he discovers that he overestimated the job and himself, resulting in the tree falling in a deep ditch! Luckily, Beresford the Crane has a plan to aid the Number One Engine! Will they be able to plant the biggest tree before the end of the holiday?
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: What's in a Name?
added.description: When Cranky gets overwhelmed on a busy and blustery day at Brendam Docks, he accidentally gets Riff and Jiff's names confused, sending them on opposite deliveries. An observant Thomas hears the mistake, but does not correct the crankier-than-usual crane -- thinking, grown-ups don't make mistakes! Thomas is proven wrong, however, when he ends up at Whiff's Recycling Plant and old tires are delivered to McColl's Farm because of Cranky's error. After calming the chaos in both places, Thomas learns that it is important to speak up and tell someone they are making a mistake --- even if it is a grown-up!

added.title: The Joke is on Thomas

added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Lost and Found
added.description: When Thomas helps Nia make a delivery to the beach in Norramby, he insists he knows a shortcut and leads the way! But it turns out his memory isn't as good as he… remembered.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Thomas' Day Off
added.description: When all the trains but Thomas get deliveries, he's left to spend the day alone. With the help of an old boxcar and a battered beachball... an adventure unfolds.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Fruit & Vegetables
added.description: On the hunt to discover the difference between fruits and vegetables, Blippi finds himself as a contestant in a community garden game show! Game show host Slim Cucumber quizzes Blippi on his knowledge of fruits and vegetables. Will Blippi know the answers?

added.title: Chocolate Factory
added.description: Blippi's love for chocolate makes him wonder "How are chocolate bars made?" They head into a chocolate factory to find out, get a tour from Bard the Chocolate Bar, and FETCH gets a close-up look at the chocolate-making process!

added.title: Australia Kangaroo

added.title: Sneeze
added.description: What is making Blippi sneeze? What makes anyone sneeze? Blippi shrinks down and flies up a nose to find out! A very mischievous piece of pollen demonstrates how to make a sneeze happen, resulting in Blippi himself getting blown away by a giant sneeze!

added.title: Snowflake
added.description: It's an icy day, and a very cold Blippi heads to the sky to find out how snowflakes are made. Way up high in the winter clouds he helps Mimi, an athletic dust particle, achieve her goal to build up enough ice crystals and transform into a unique and awesome snowflake. Way to be original Mimi!

added.title: Bee a Bee dance

added.title: The Growing Song

added.title: No Monsters Scared of the Dark

added.title: Accidents Happen Boo Boo Song

added.title: Bath Song

added.title: Taz You Like It

added.title: Band Together

added.title: War of the Weirds
